}} 'Mars Science Laboratory' ('MSL') is a robotic space probe mission to Mars
launched by NASA on November 26, 2011, which successfully
landed [[Curiosity rover|Curiosity]], a Mars rover, in Gale Crater on August 6,
2012. The overall objectives include investigating Mars'
habitability, studying its climate and geology, and collecting data for a manned
mission to Mars. The rover carries a variety of scientific
instruments designed by an international team.
